  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "It\u2019s time to show SL bowlers, batters who they are: Mahela",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former Sri Lankan skipper Mahela Jayawardene said that it\u2019s time for Sri Lanka bowlers to show the class and batters to show who they are on the field, ahead of the T-20 match between Sri Lanka and Bangladesh at the Asia Cup today.",
        "He made these remarks on Tweeter in response to a comment made by Bangladesh Coach Khaled Mahmud.",
        "Responding to a statement made by Sri Lanka captain Dasun Shanaka that Bangladesh has only two world class bowlers compared to Afghanistan, Bangladesh Coach Khaled Mahmud said yesterday that he doesn\u2019t think Sri Lanka has any world class bowlers.",
        "\u201cI don\u2019t know why Dasun Shanaka said such a thing. I heard that he said Bangladesh does not have world class bowlers except Shakib Al Hassan and Mustafizur. In fact, I do not see a single world class bowler in the Sri Lankan camp,\u201d Mahmud said during a press conference on yesterday.",
        "He said at least Bangladesh have two world class bowlers. \u201cBut Sri Lanka does not even have anyone who bears the quality of Shakib and Mustafizur in their side,\u201d Mahmud added.",
        "\u201cLooks like it\u2019s time for Sri Lanka's bowlers to show the class and batters to show who they are on the field,\" Mahela tweeted."
      ],
